# Simple iOS Calculator

This repository contains a basic iOS calculator app built using fundamental Swift and SwiftUI. The project focuses on core programming concepts, basic user interface layouts, and simple state management.

## How to Run This Project

To run this app and test it interactively, follow these steps:

1. Open the Swift Playgrounds app on an iPad or Mac (or open Xcode on a Mac).
2. Create a new App project.
3. Open the ContentView.swift file.
4. Replace all the default code inside ContentView.swift with the Swift code provided in this repository.
5. Use the live preview panel on the right side of the screen to interact with the calculator buttons and test the math logic.

